text: Compared to the movie the book is way better. I read the book first and then watched the movie and I'm glad I did. I found that Idris and Kate did not have chemistry between them playing the characters from the book. There was a lot of changes from the book in the movie which were not necessary and in my opinion ruined the plot. Not wanting to spoil it for others who may go and watch this, but when reading the book I was sympathetic to Ben's emotional journey from beginning to end and his experience with Ashley through the mountains.  Watching the movie tainted that and I was disappointed that the movie did not capture the essence of the book at all.  Having said that, whilst reading the book I did think to myself how the plot could be made into a movie that would be enjoyable to watch, due to what ACTUALLY happens in the book. Not all books can be made into movies that are as good as the books themselves.... This is one of them.
